# Figma Clone — Project Overview

A browser-based Figma clone with an embedded Gen-AI plugin engine. Users design on a canvas and invoke AI to generate custom "plugins" — both canvas actions and a live control panel — on the fly.

## Tech Stack

- **Framework**: Next.js 16 (App Router) with React 19
- **Language**: TypeScript (strict mode, ES2017 target)
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS 3 + Figma design tokens (CSS custom properties)
- **State**: Zustand + Immer (event-sourced, undo/redo); separate transient store for 60fps drag/resize
- **UI primitives**: Radix UI / shadcn + FigUI3 web components (`@rogieking/figui3`)
- **Canvas**: Custom DOM-based renderer (world/screen coordinate system, not HTML canvas element)
- **Gen-AI**: LLM returns JSON `{ actions, ui }` — actions execute on canvas, `ui` defines a declarative control panel

## Path Aliases

- `@/*` maps to `./src/*`
- `@fpl/tokens` maps to `./src/lib/color-theme`

## Key Directories

```
src/
  app/            Next.js App Router (layout, page, API routes)
  components/     Shared UI — canvas, panels, toolbars, sidebars
  core/           State (stores), hooks, services, utils
  features/       Feature modules (gen-ai is the primary one)
  contexts/       React contexts (Theme, Navigation)
  types/          Shared TypeScript types (canvas.ts is central)
  hooks/          Global hooks (persistence, cursors)
  lib/            Color theme tokens, utilities
  styles/         CSS tokens, global styles
```

## Architecture

- **Event-sourced store**: All mutations go through `dispatch(createEvent(...))`. A reducer (`applyEventToState`) applies them to an Immer draft. Undo/redo stacks are maintained automatically.
- **Transient store**: High-frequency state (drag positions, resize) lives outside Immer to avoid re-render overhead.
- **Gen-AI pipeline**: User prompt -> LLM -> JSON response -> `action-adapter.ts` executes canvas actions + `CustomControlsPopover.tsx` renders the UI spec. Generator functions allow controls to re-run actions live without another LLM call. Auto-generate ("+" button) reverse-engineers controls for existing objects. AI shimmer animation activates on all LLM-calling paths.
- **Fill system**: `Fill` is a discriminated union (`solid | linear-gradient | radial-gradient | image`). All fill mutations go through `action-adapter.ts handleSetFill`. Opacity updates must preserve the existing fill type.
